<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Sat, 16 May 2026 12:56:02 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>碧昂丝和泰勒·斯威夫特的音乐以及数十首其他“音频宝藏”已添加到国家唱片登记处</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/music-from-taylor-swift-and-beyonce-plus-dozens-of-other-audio-treasures-added-to-national-recording-registry-180988754/</link><description>美国国会图书馆国家播放列表中最新添加的 25 首歌曲被认为“因其在国家录制的声音遗产中的文化、历史或美学重要性而值得永远保存”</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 21:32:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/music-from-taylor-swift-and-beyonce-plus-dozens-of-other-audio-treasures-added-to-national-recording-registry-180988754/</guid></item><item><title>在巨大的铁器时代宝藏中发现了英国部落强大女王可能使用过的“神奇”镜子，目前正在展出</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-magical-mirror-the-powerful-queen-of-a-british-tribe-may-have-used-goes-on-display-as-part-of-britains-largest-iron-age-hoard-180988751/</link><description>参观约克郡博物馆的游客可以看到来自梅尔森比宝库的文物，其历史可以追溯到公元一世纪，这些文物改写了罗马入侵时期英国财富和权力的故事</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 20:44:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-magical-mirror-the-powerful-queen-of-a-british-tribe-may-have-used-goes-on-display-as-part-of-britains-largest-iron-age-hoard-180988751/</guid></item><item><title>无意识思维是否意识到周围环境？新研究表明麻醉大脑可以处理无意中听到的单词</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/is-the-unconscious-mind-aware-of-its-surroundings-new-research-suggests-anesthetized-brains-can-process-overheard-words-180988710/</link><description>七名参与者的电极暂时植入对学习很重要的大脑结构中。在麻醉状态下，他们的神经细胞学会了区分不同的声音，甚至可以预测短语中即将出现的单词</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 15:40:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/is-the-unconscious-mind-aware-of-its-surroundings-new-research-suggests-anesthetized-brains-can-process-overheard-words-180988710/</guid></item><item><title>新的稀有鸽子幼崽是已灭绝野生鸟类的“希望之源”，也是拯救它们的雄心勃勃的计划向前迈出的一步</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-rare-dove-hatchlings-are-a-source-of-hope-for-the-extinct-in-the-wild-birds-and-a-step-forward-in-the-ambitious-project-to-save-them-180988730/</link><description>自 1972 年以来，索科罗斑鸠就没有在野外记录过，但环保人士表示，由于长期的重新引入努力，这种情况可能会在短短几年内发生变化</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 15:07:38 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-rare-dove-hatchlings-are-a-source-of-hope-for-the-extinct-in-the-wild-birds-and-a-step-forward-in-the-ambitious-project-to-save-them-180988730/</guid></item><item><title>一名男子在泰国的一个池塘附近发现了奇怪的岩石。它们原来是一种巨大的新恐龙物种的骨头</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-man-spotted-strange-looking-rocks-near-a-pond-in-thailand-they-turned-out-to-be-the-bones-of-a-massive-new-dinosaur-species-180988744/</link><description>古生物学家将这种长颈食草生物称为“Nagatitan chaiyaphumensis”。这是泰国第 14 种被命名的恐龙，它可能是东南亚迄今为止发现的最大的恐龙</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-man-spotted-strange-looking-rocks-near-a-pond-in-thailand-they-turned-out-to-be-the-bones-of-a-massive-new-dinosaur-species-180988744/</guid></item><item><title>尼安德特人也有蛀牙，新的研究表明他们会像现代牙医一样钻进牙齿来治疗蛀牙</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/neanderthals-got-cavities-too-and-new-research-suggests-they-drilled-into-their-teeth-to-treat-them-just-like-modern-dentists-180988746/</link><description>研究人员出土了一颗 59,000 年前的尼安德特人臼齿，它显示出牙科手术的迹象，这一发现将最早的牙科手术证据推迟了大约 45,000 年</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 13:34:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/neanderthals-got-cavities-too-and-new-research-suggests-they-drilled-into-their-teeth-to-treat-them-just-like-modern-dentists-180988746/</guid></item><item><title>弗里达·卡洛 (Frida Kahlo) 和迭戈·里维拉 (Diego Rivera) 在受希腊神话和墨西哥魔幻现实主义启发的大都会歌剧院中自唱至死</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/frida-kahlo-and-diego-rivera-sing-themselves-to-death-in-an-opera-at-the-met-inspired-by-greek-mythology-and-mexican-magical-realism-180988742/</link><description>全新制作的全西班牙歌剧《El Último Sueño de Frida y Diego》本周在纽约上演，而现代艺术博物馆的合作展览则探讨了这部歌剧背后的艺术</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 20:23:20 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/frida-kahlo-and-diego-rivera-sing-themselves-to-death-in-an-opera-at-the-met-inspired-by-greek-mythology-and-mexican-magical-realism-180988742/</guid></item><item><title>最新研究表明，这种鱼会搭在蝠鲼的“屁眼”上</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-fish-hitches-rides-in-manta-rays-buttholes-according-to-new-research-180988736/</link><description>科学家怀疑这种行为可能会伤害蝠鲼，这表明鲳鱼与其宿主之间存在复杂的关系，有时可能是寄生关系</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 19:56:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-fish-hitches-rides-in-manta-rays-buttholes-according-to-new-research-180988736/</guid></item><item><title>不开玩笑，梅尔·布鲁克斯在 100 岁生日之前将他的搞笑档案捐赠给国家喜剧中心</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/no-joke-ahead-of-his-100th-birthday-mel-brooks-donates-his-hilarious-archive-to-the-national-comedy-center-180988741/</link><description>属于“2000 岁老人”和 EGOT 获奖者的数千条笔记、故事板、早期脚本和照片将与露西尔·鲍尔、琼·里弗斯和乔治·卡林的材料一起加入</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 19:21:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/no-joke-ahead-of-his-100th-birthday-mel-brooks-donates-his-hilarious-archive-to-the-national-comedy-center-180988741/</guid></item><item><title>在白令海峡修建大坝能否使地球免受气候变化的影响？</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-building-a-dam-across-the-bering-straight-save-the-planet-from-some-effects-of-climate-change-180988725/</link><description>一项初步研究表明，封锁俄罗斯和阿拉斯加之间的水道可能有助于关键洋流系统的生存。但可能会产生潜在的不可预见的后果，特别是对海洋生态系统</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 16:05:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-building-a-dam-across-the-bering-straight-save-the-planet-from-some-effects-of-climate-change-180988725/</guid></item><item><title>新研究表明，胎儿在子宫内就可以从母亲那里“感染”哈欠</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/fetuses-can-catch-yawns-from-their-mothers-while-still-in-the-womb-new-research-suggests-180988735/</link><description>打哈欠被认为是一种社交行为。尽管众所周知胎儿会打哈欠，但科学家们不确定这是否是一种独立的反射，或者他们是否能以某种方式检测到来自母亲的暗示</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/fetuses-can-catch-yawns-from-their-mothers-while-still-in-the-womb-new-research-suggests-180988735/</guid></item><item><title>智人真的比尼安德特人聪明吗？新研究表明，不同的头骨形状并不一定意味着不同的大脑容量</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/did-homo-sapiens-really-outsmart-neanderthals-different-skull-shapes-didnt-necessarily-mean-unequal-brain-capacity-new-research-shows-180988738/</link><description>美国和中国研究人员的一项研究表明，尼安德特人和早期现代人类可能具有相似的认知能力</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 21:29:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/did-homo-sapiens-really-outsmart-neanderthals-different-skull-shapes-didnt-necessarily-mean-unequal-brain-capacity-new-research-shows-180988738/</guid></item><item><title>新研究表明，经常听歌或画画放松实际上可能会延缓细胞衰老</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-relaxation-of-listening-to-a-song-or-drawing-a-picture-may-actually-slow-cellular-aging-new-research-show-180988734/</link><description>根据一项新的研究，每周接触艺术的人比每年只接触一次或两次艺术的人“生理上”年轻一岁左右</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 20:39:43 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-relaxation-of-listening-to-a-song-or-drawing-a-picture-may-actually-slow-cellular-aging-new-research-show-180988734/</guid></item><item><title>这幅文艺复兴时期的画作蜿蜒曲折，从希特勒的慕尼黑公寓到美国记者的家，再到伦敦国家美术馆</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-renaissance-painting-took-a-winding-path-from-hitlers-munich-apartment-to-an-american-journalists-home-to-the-national-gallery-in-london-180988733/</link><description>一位艺术历史学家最近在希特勒旧公寓的一张罕见照片中发现了 16 世纪的艺术品，该照片印在 1978 年的家具目录中</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 19:08:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-renaissance-painting-took-a-winding-path-from-hitlers-munich-apartment-to-an-american-journalists-home-to-the-national-gallery-in-london-180988733/</guid></item><item><title>这种微小的真菌在美国宇航局的灭菌协议中幸存下来，并且有可能足以污染火星</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-microscopic-fungus-survived-nasas-sterilization-protocols-and-is-hardy-enough-to-potentially-contaminate-mars-180988728/</link><description>这些微生物是从该机构的洁净室中收集的，专家们在洁净室中精心控制的环境中建造航天器。调查结果揭示了该机构在防止长期搭便车者方面的程序存在缺陷</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 18:57:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-microscopic-fungus-survived-nasas-sterilization-protocols-and-is-hardy-enough-to-potentially-contaminate-mars-180988728/</guid></item><item><title>观看 17 张复杂的显微镜照片，让微型世界变得无比巨大。他们赢得了年度最佳形象大赛</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-17-intricate-microscope-photographs-that-make-the-miniature-world-immense-they-won-the-evident-image-of-the-year-contest-180988722/</link><description>第六届年度竞赛展示了科学显微成像，照亮了自然界的微小部分，从单个细胞到节肢动物、硅藻和斑马鱼大脑</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 18:45:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-17-intricate-microscope-photographs-that-make-the-miniature-world-immense-they-won-the-evident-image-of-the-year-contest-180988722/</guid></item><item><title>这些海藻在海浪扰动时会发光。他们的生物发光可以为未来的无电灯供电</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-marine-algae-glow-when-waves-disturb-them-their-bioluminescence-could-power-electricity-free-lamps-of-the-future-180988721/</link><description>这些单细胞生物通常只会闪烁几毫秒，但研究人员找到了维持其发光的方法。这项技术有一天可以用来照亮机器人在深海或太空中的道路</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 15:43:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-marine-algae-glow-when-waves-disturb-them-their-bioluminescence-could-power-electricity-free-lamps-of-the-future-180988721/</guid></item><item><title>新数据显示，密歇根州罗亚尔岛国家公园的狼群数量激增，数量达到近 50 年来的最高水平</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/wolves-are-thriving-at-michigans-isle-royale-national-park-reaching-their-highest-numbers-in-almost-50-years-new-data-suggests-180988727/</link><description>科学家估计，目前有 37 只驼鹿在崎岖的群岛上漫步，这导致了驼鹿数量的减少。但捕食者与猎物的比例可能会趋于稳定</description><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/wolves-are-thriving-at-michigans-isle-royale-national-park-reaching-their-highest-numbers-in-almost-50-years-new-data-suggests-180988727/</guid></item><item><title>马铃薯不仅为安第斯山脉的古代土著社区提供食物，美味的块茎还重塑了人们的 DNA</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/potatoes-didnt-just-feed-ancient-indigenous-communities-in-the-andes-the-tasty-tubers-also-reshaped-peoples-dna-180988732/</link><description>一项新的研究发现，生活在现在秘鲁境内的安第斯土著人有一个名为 AMY1 的基因的额外副本，该基因有助于身体消化淀粉</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 21:13:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/potatoes-didnt-just-feed-ancient-indigenous-communities-in-the-andes-the-tasty-tubers-also-reshaped-peoples-dna-180988732/</guid></item><item><title>NASA 刚刚上传了 Artemis 2 任务的 12,000 多张令人惊叹的照片。这是我们最喜欢的一些</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasa-just-uploaded-more-than-12000-stunning-photos-from-the-artemis-2-mission-here-are-a-few-of-our-favorites-180988697/</link><description>尽管此次任务的四名宇航员在太空中向地球发送了一些照片，但大多数照片在返回地球后都需要通过物理存储卡传送</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 20:32:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasa-just-uploaded-more-than-12000-stunning-photos-from-the-artemis-2-mission-here-are-a-few-of-our-favorites-180988697/</guid></item></channel></rss>